In the first post, Pursell wrote that he&rsquo;s &ldquo;walking away&rdquo; from the CW superhero drama, which premiered in 2016. &ldquo;Deal isn&rsquo;t done. I have no interest. Whatever cash they throw on the corporate level,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;The studio does not care.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Then he followed that up with another post claiming that his original post &ldquo;was a joke and the press went nuts.&rdquo; He said he didn&rsquo;t have any problems with the studio, Warner Bros. Television. &ldquo;Truth is yes I&rsquo;m leaving [Legends of Tomorrow] but will come back periodically,&rdquo; he wrote. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s a handshake deal with my boss Phil Klemmer.&rdquo;
